<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>The College awards credit for the subject examinations of the Advanced Placement (AP) and the College Level Examination Program (CLEP) and the International Baccalaureate (IB).Credit also may be awarded on the basis of institutional examinations. Ordinarily, such examinations should be taken prior to enrollment at Brevard. For more information concerning AP, CLEP, or IB, students should contact the Office of Admission, the chair of the appropriate division, or their faculty advisors.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.brevard.edu/academics/registrar" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

